5:
Sweet Sally's software! You people are 
like bug magnets!
6:
They're not supposed to be that 
vicious, you know. Especially not 
towards organics. You flip a wrong 
switch somewhere?
12:
Really now? Hm. Well, at least we 
managed to tap dance past security. 
You'll be safe here.
16:
The streets and walls are ill-kept. 
Regis, what is this place?
23:
The Lost City. A glorified name, really. 
It's nothing more than a jumble of 
worker's shacks thrown up while 
reconstruction was going on.
24:
And once the grand megalopolis was 
open for business, they left this joint to 
dust, decay... and those poor 
creatures.
27: H-hey... You got any memory bytes?
28:
Please. We're starving... We need some 
bytes.
31:
Here. It's not much, but it'll tide you 
over. A few tunes to fill your heads.
41:
They're trying to fiddle with their 
memories.
44: But there's a firewall. Why would they—
56:
Droids who've had their memories 
wiped. As punishment for committing 
a crime.
59:
We decided that rehabilitation through 
pain was uncouth. So we clean off their 
slates instead. Tabula rasa, and all 
that.
60:
But each time they're reset, there's a 
hole in them that grows larger. Get 
reset enough times, and a droid will 
become hollow. Incomplete and 
forever dogged by fear.
64: You've got a twisted idea of mercy.
66:
Yes, but look on the bright side. They're 
in no condition to report us. Not to 
mention, I DID just break the law for 
their sakes.
74:
To droids, memory files and sound 
synthesizers—what you would call the 
mind and voice—are sacred.
76:
It's a crime to alter them, and access is 
basically restricted.  But hollows…
78:
They've had their firewalls torn down. 
'Course, someone else's memories, 
they're nowhere near as solid as your 
own.
80:
Got as much weight to them as a half-
remembered dream... But for the 
starving souls, it's the best they can 
get.
87:
Mana hackers detected. All involved 
parties are to desist at once.
90:
Security!
That's some lousy luck. Usually, cats 
don't come this far into the rat's nest…
95:
No. Can't those bunny ears hear? 
They came for the hackers.
102:
They'll have their memories wiped. 
In the delusional hope that, this time, 
they’ll make a brand new start of it.
115: Hey! What do you think you're doing?!
126:
Sizzling circuits... If you lot had a death 
wish, why bother bringing me along in 
the first place?
